The **Mistral Instruct v0.3** format is simpler:
- User turns are wrapped in `[INST]`/`[/INST]`
- System messages are prepended to the **first** user turn (not standalone)
- `eos_token` (`</s>`) is appended after each assistant turn
- No `[SYSTEM_PROMPT]`, no `[TOOL_CALLS]`, no reasoning tokens

Currently this format falls through to the autoparser. A dedicated handler allows more reliable content-only parsing.

