## Step-by-Step Implementation

### Step 1 — Create the Jinja template

**New file**: `models/templates/mistralai-Mistral-7B-Instruct-v0.3.jinja`

```jinja
{%- if messages[0]['role'] == 'system' %}
    {%- set system_message = messages[0]['content'] %}
    {%- set loop_messages = messages[1:] %}
{%- else %}
    {%- set loop_messages = messages %}
{%- endif %}
{{- bos_token }}
{%- for message in loop_messages %}
    {%- if message['role'] == 'user' %}
        {%- if loop.first and system_message is defined %}
            {{- '[INST] ' + system_message + '\n\n' + message['content'] + ' [/INST]' }}
        {%- else %}
            {{- '[INST] ' + message['content'] + ' [/INST]' }}
        {%- endif %}
    {%- elif message['role'] == 'assistant' %}
        {{- message['content'] + eos_token }}
    {%- else %}
        {{- raise_exception('Only user and assistant roles are supported, with the exception of an initial optional system message!') }}
    {%- endif %}
{%- endfor %}
```

Key properties that drive detection:
- Contains `[INST]` ✓
- Does **not** contain `[SYSTEM_PROMPT]` → distinguishes from Ministral 3
- Does **not** contain `[TOOL_CALLS]` → distinguishes from Nemo (`mistralai-Mistral-Nemo-Instruct-2407.jinja`)

---

### Step 2 — Add the handler function in `common/chat.cpp`

**Insertion point**: Between line 1632 (end of `common_chat_extra_context()`) and line 1634 (start of `common_chat_try_specialized_template()`).

Reuse existing static helper: `common_chat_template_direct_apply_impl()` (already used by all other handlers in this file; no import needed).

```cpp
// Mistral Instruct v0.3 - simple [INST]/[/INST] format, no tool calls, no reasoning.
// System message (if present) is prepended to the first user turn.
// Assistant turns are terminated with eos_token.
static common_chat_params common_chat_params_init_mistral_instruct_v3(
        const common_chat_template &          tmpl,
        const autoparser::generation_params & inputs) {
    common_chat_params data;
    data.prompt = common_chat_template_direct_apply_impl(tmpl, inputs);
    data.format = COMMON_CHAT_FORMAT_CONTENT_ONLY;
    return data;
}
```

No grammar, no PEG parser, no preserved tokens — the format emits plain text only.

